    "recap_headline": "TCU",
    "recap_text": "TEMPE, Ariz.\n\u2013\nColton Griffin\ngave No. 17 TCU a late lead, then threw out the tying run at home to end the game, securing the Horned Frogs' 5-4 win over Arizona State in its Big 12 opener Friday night.\nMason Brassfield\nturned in his second straight quality start on the mound.\nThe Rundown\nTied at three in the eighth,\nColton Griffin\ndelivered a two-run, two-out single to give the Horned Frogs a 5-3 lead.\nWith the Frogs clinging to a 5-4 lead and facing runners on the corners with one out, it was once again Griffin who answered the call. On a fly ball to shallow left, the Sun Devil runner took off for home. Griffin's throw to the plate was spot on to\nBrady Dallimore\n, who tagged out the tying run to end the game.\nThe game was a pitcher's dual through six innings. Arizona State took a 1-0 lead in the first on a one-out home run. TCU answered the home run in the third with a rocket off the bat of Dallimore.\nIt was TCU that finally broke the stalemate in the seventh. With two in scoring position and two outs, the Sun Devils intentionally walked\nCole Cramer\nto load the bases.\nSawyer Strosnider\nmade them pay with a two-run single to left for a 3-1 lead. Arizona State answered in the bottom of the inning with a pair of RBI-pinch hits to tie the game at three, setting up the wild finish.\nMason Brassfield\nwent six innings, allowing a run on four hits. He walked two and struck out eight.\nNate Stern\n(2-0) picked up the win in relief, allowing a run on an hit. He walked one and struck out two in 1 1/3 innings.\nTanner Sagouspe\nearned his first save at TCU with a scoreless inning.\nStat of the Game:\n4 \u2013\nTCU turned four double plays in the game, none of the conventional variety. The Frogs executed two strike 'em out, throw 'em out double plays and doubled off two base runners.\nNotes:\n\u2022 TCU allowed a first inning run for just the seventh time this season.\n\u2022 TCU homered in a game for the 12\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 TCU was outhit by its opponent for the ninth time this season.\n\u2022 TCU played errorless baseball for the fourth time this season.\n\u2022 TCU stole a base for the 13\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 The TCU pitching staff recorded double-digit strikeouts (12) for the ninth time this season.\n\u2022\nMason Brassfield\nregistered his second career quality start.\n\u2022\nTanner Sagouspe\npicked up his first save at TCU and the 17\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nCole Cramer\nhas reached safely in 14 straight games.\n\u2022\nSawyer Strosnider\nhas reached safely in 33 straight games dating back to last season.\n\u2022 Strosnider tallied his fourth multi-RBI game of the season and the 17\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nChase Brunson\nhas reached safely in all 17 games and 18 games dating back to last season.\n\u2022\nNolan Traeger\nhas reached safely in 11 straight games.\n\u2022\nRob Liddington\nhas reached safely in nine straight games.\n\u2022\nBrady Dallimore\nhit his second career home run.\n\u2022 Dallimore recorded his second career multi-hit game.\n\u2022\nColton Griffin\ntallied his first multi-RBI game of the season and the ninth of his career.\n\u2022 Griffin and Brunson registered outfield assists in the game.\nNext Up:\nWith the win, TCU improves to 11-6 on the season and 1-0 in Big 12 play.\u00a0The Horned Frogs and Sun Devils will meet in Game 2 of the series on Saturday night. Game time is set for 8:30 p.m. (CT).\nLance Davis\nwill get the start for the Frogs. The entire series will be televised on ESPN+."
